# CAN Architecture Quick Reference

## TPMS
- TPMS is polled from the **BCM via Mode 22** (PIDs 0x2813–0x2816) every 30s
- CAN frame 0x340 is **ambient temperature only** (PCMmsg17, byte 7 signed × 0.25 °C) — NOT TPMS
- Formula: `(((256×A)+B)/3 + 22/3) × 0.145 PSI`

## Correct CAN IDs (commonly confused)
| Signal | Correct ID | Wrong (stale) | Source |
|--------|-----------|---------------|--------|
| Fuel level | 0x380 | ~~0x34A~~ | RS_HS.dbc PCMmsg30, Motorola 10-bit |
| Wheel speeds | 0x190 | ~~0x215~~ | RS_HS.dbc ABSmsg03 |
| PTU temp | 0x0F8 byte7 | ~~0x2C2~~ | RS_HS.dbc PCMmsg07 |
| Ambient temp | 0x340 / 0x1A4 | — | 0x340 = PCMmsg17, 0x1A4 = MS-CAN bridged |

## Polling intervals
All ECU polling is **30 seconds**: PCM (0x7E0), BCM (0x726), AWD (0x703). There is no 10s interval.

